]. Approximately 70% of marine plastic debris is deposited in sediments, 15% floats in coastal areas and the remainder float on the surface seawater (
). Microplastics will be accumulated in the global ocean circulation, since some of them are less dense than seawater and float on the sea surface, and the converging sea currents concentrate and retain debris for a long time [
]. According to the surveys, there are only at least 7000 tonnes of plastic debris on the surface of the high seas [
], but at least 4.8 million tonnes of plastic debris enter the marine environment each year [
