3.3. Bioaccumulation and Bioavailability
The two important indexes to access the impacts of MPs to organisms are bioaccumulation and bioavailability [
]. There are interactions between MPs and organisms in the marine environment [
]. Microplastics can be ingested directly by marine organisms or transferred and accumulated in the food web from lower trophic organisms to higher trophic organisms, and the higher the trophic level, the more microplastics may be enriched in the organism [
]. In addition, toxic pollutants could be transported and accumulated in organisms along with microplastics through the ingestion, which has been demonstrated during experimental

