The factors involved in plastic biodegradability depend not only on the ability of microorganisms but also on the characteristics and surface structure of the material, such as the roughness, electrostatic interactions, topography, hydrophobicity, and free energy [
]. In addition, various environmental factors, such as oxygen level, temperature, humidity, salinity, and limitation of light have an important impact on the biodegradation of plastics [
