). In 2012, there were few rowan berries, while in 2016, rowan berries were far more abundant. This indicates that apple fruit moth populations were in a growth phase in 2016, suggesting that an interval of maximum four years is necessary to complete an outbreak cycle. This is consistent with previous results showing that rowanberry masting occurred every 2–4 years [
